<TD Width=490 valign=top>
<center><IMG SRC="gif/hdlib.gif"></center>
<P>
<a href="PR/lfc.html">Liberty Financial Companies (NYSE: L)</A> is an organization dedicated to the Internet and electronic commerce. We believe that the Internet has the potential to become one of the most important developments in the financial services industry this decade. We are integrating the Internet into our existing business model to provide customers and distributors with secure, direct access to their accounts, product information and market data.<P>

Liberty Financial is taking Internet investing to the next level. More than just electronic brochures, our Web sites are examples of personalized experiences that allow Liberty Financial's operating companies to interact with their customers on a one-to-one basis -- in secure, private contexts.<P>

Through the Liberty Financial corporate Web site, you have access to the Web sites of each of our different operating units: Stein Roe Mutual Funds, Keyport, Colonial, Newport Pacific, Independent Financial Marketing and Liberty Asset Management. <P>

Liberty Financial also maintains an award-winning Web site -- The Young Investor Web Site -- designed to teach <a href="http://www.younginvestor.com">kids</a> and their <a href="http://www.younginvestor.com/parents.html">parents</a> about money and investing as part of its Liberty Financial Young Investor Program. <P>

For a complete look at our company, please view the online version of <a href="index2.html">Liberty Financial Companies' 1996 Annual Report</a><br>
